# INST377 \- Lab 7

This is the 7th lab Assignment for INST377. The goal of this lab is to focus on ASync Function in Javascript.  
This lab will involve using an API call to look up some books and create some dynamic elements while the data loads.  
This will be a great example of an Async use case and demonstrating how it could be used to inform users while data is loading.

**Github Classroom Link: [https://classroom.github.com/a/4SGuVKTK](https://classroom.github.com/a/4SGuVKTK)**

# Requirements \- (24 pts):

The Page must have the following Sections:

1. Before Search (9 pts)  
   1. Create a Title (2pts)  
   2. Create a Form  
      1. Text Type Input (2pts)  
      2. Submit Button (2pts)  
   3. On Submit call the Search Books Function (3pts)  
2. During Search (9 pts)  
   1. Show a Loading Text \- Only During the API Call, not before the search button is clicked, and not after the results are retrieved (7 pts)  
   2. API Endpoint (2 pts)

```
https://openlibrary.org/search.json?title=${bookName}
```

When putting the book name remember you must use \+ instead of space. An example is `Lord of the Rings` would become `Lord+Of+The+Rings`

You can read more about the API here: [https://openlibrary.org/dev/docs/api/search](https://openlibrary.org/dev/docs/api/search) 

3. After Search (6 pts)  
   1. Show a Table with a list of Title and Authors from the API Response  
4. Notes:  
   1. Remember the table should not be visible Before the user inputs something in the search  
   2. The Loading message should **only** be visible while you are waiting for the response from the API
